    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#8217;m really surprise that so few of you had never tasted before raw escarole.</>In Catalonia it&#8217;s very preciated and we make a very nice salad called Xató (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xat%C3%B3" rel="nofollow ugc">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xat%C3%B3</a>). It has escarole, tuna, anxovies, cod, and Xató dressing -olive oil, vinegar, hazelnuts, almonds, salt and nyora (a catalan sweet capsicum)-.</p>
