  <li id="comment-6549" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">emily</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2007/02/what-the-salad-bowl-has-joined-together/#comment-6549"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2007-03-31T23:41:00-04:00">Saturday, March 31, 2007 at 11:41 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>My escarole was bitter, but still very good!  I just bought it for the first time (by accident).  When I tasted it plain, it was definitely bitter, about on par with lettuce stems in summer.  I then added a dressing of equal parts pomegranate molasses, balsamic vinegar &#038; olive oil.  I had no problem eating it all, the assertive dressing stood up to the bitter.  But don&#8217;t feed this to your friends who are used to iceberg lettuce&#8230;  My escarole was purchased from whole foods at the end of March, and grown in mexico.  Maybe it changes with the season.</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
